This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with audio data. Additionally, the paper uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for feature extraction, which is a common technique in machine learning and could place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also discusses optimization techniques, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
